    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I got a bit carried away with the goblin analogy. To break it down simply, the indemnification section means that if you (the consultant) breach any terms or conditions of the agreement, the client will not be held liable for any damages or losses resulting from that breach. In other words, the client can seek compensation from you, the consultant, if you fail to fulfill your obligations under the agreement. This can include costs, expenses, and even attorneys' fees associated with defending against a claim. Think of it like a safety net for the client, protecting them from financial losses due to your actions.",
