    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, thanks. Is there anything else in this specific clause that I should watch out for? Like, are there certain types of losses or 'hidden' issues that might be particularly dangerous for me to agree to?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "One thing to be cautious about is the scope of the indemnification. It's a broad clause that covers \"any and all\" losses, which can be a bit ambiguous. It's like trying to catch a slippery fish - it's easy to get caught up in the wording and end up covering losses that you might not have anticipated.\n\nFor example, if the agreement is related to a specific project or service, you might want to clarify whether the indemnification only applies to losses related to that project, or if it's a blanket clause that covers all your services. It's also worth reviewing the language to see if there are any exclusions or limitations on what's covered.\n\nAdditionally, you might want to consider the duration of the indemnification. Is it only applicable during the term of the agreement, or does it extend beyond that? It's like trying to protect yourself from a goblin attack that might happen years after the initial battle.",
